## Step 3: Art standards (enforce these on every change)

### Sprites
- **Size**: 32×32 px (heroes/enemies), tile-multiple for buildings (e.g. castle = 96×96)
- **Format**: PNG RGBA, pixel-aligned
- **Scaling**: nearest-neighbor only — never anti-aliased, never bilinear
- **Naming**: `frame_000.png`, `frame_001.png` (zero-padded, sorted)
- **Silhouette-first**: strong readable silhouette beats color detail
- **Outline**: 1px near-black selective outline on unit sprites
- **Class accents**: Warrior=blue, Ranger=green, Rogue=steel/gray, Wizard=purple

### Procedural sprites (when no PNG exists)
- Game auto-generates placeholder sprites when asset files are missing — this is intentional safety
- Procedural generation must be **deterministic**: seed from tile coord, entity ID, or building type — never wall-clock time or `random.random()`
- Cache generated surfaces — never allocate per-frame
- Use `zlib.crc32()` for hashing tile coords into determinism seeds (not Python `hash()`)

### Animation frame counts (hero set standard)
- `idle`: 6 frames
- `walk`: 8 frames
- `attack`: 6 frames (1–2 anticipation, 1 strike, 2–3 recover)
- `hurt`: 4 frames
- `inside`: 6 frames (bubble/icon style)

### VFX rules
- All VFX is **render-only** — never affects simulation state
- Projectile lifetime: 250–450ms (readable mid-flight)
- Debris: 10–25 pieces, 2–3px chunks, scatter based on building footprint, no fade-out
- Dust/puffs: capped emission rate, deterministic seed from entity ID + tick

